HEADWORD: Antipathetical
<hw>An`ti*pa*thet"ic*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Having a natural contrariety, or constitutional aversion, to a
thing; characterized by antipathy; -- often followed by
<xex>to</xex>.</def> <rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

